# Manual testing instructions (Jaimie-friendly)

Whenever asking the human (Jaimie) to manually test anything:

## Always assume

- Jaimie is **not deep in the sprint context**.
- Jaimie has **limited developer experience** and needs very explicit “what to look for”.

## Required format for any manual test request

- **Exact command(s)** to run from the repo root (PowerShell-compatible).
- **Duration**: how long to run it (e.g. “2 minutes”, “10 minutes”).
- **Steps**: 3–7 bullet steps, in order.
- **What to verify**: concrete pass/fail checks, phrased as observations.
- **What to do if it fails**: what to screenshot/copy, and which log/doc to reference.
- **What to review (optional)**: 1–2 specific docs/plan paths if sprint context matters.

## Example template

```text
Run:
<exact command>

Do this:
1) ...
2) ...

Verify:
- ...
- ...

If it fails:
- Copy/paste the last ~30 lines of terminal output
- Note whether you ran --no-llm or --provider mock
- Tell me what you clicked/expected vs what happened

Context to skim (2 minutes):
- .cursor/plans/<current sprint plan>.plan.md (Definition of Done section)
```

